node.text:
#story it's a long one but if you're my friend please watch.  I had a very scary experience after work yesterday and am sharing 1. Because I feel helpless to do anything else and 2. To make sure all of you,  especially the ladies, stay alert when traveling alone at night. .
.
.
.
.
.
For those who know me and consider me "strong"...im really struggling a bit with my sense of self right now.  I'll be okay, i know this isn't on me and will continue fighting the thoughts creeping in that say otherwise. .
.
.
.
.
#nyc #subway #fear #metoo #yesallwomen #iwasscared #ihatethis #safe #strong #woman #women #newyork #friday #fridaynight #travel #commute #commuter
@fabulousswamie thanks girl!  Ive never had any qualms about the subway until last night.  Definitely popped my invincible bubble.  People are scary indeed!
Omg girl. Thank God your ok. I never liked the subway. People are so scary nowadays.
@michelle.meacham yeeeeeeees indeed Michelle 💗
@365curlgirl Thank God that you are safe and Thank God for Alex
@ms.spires thank you Toya, I definitely need to see and hear this reassurance
@365curlgirl I just thank God for his mercy and that you were paying attention.
You did the right thing. We have to force people to pay attention sometimes.
@moeartistry right!? I shall name my first born Alex!  Jk.  There will be no first born lol.
I’m literally at a lost for words but I thank God your ok and that Alex was there !
@black_kat_spaz you are very right.  I should be thankful my gift if fear even kicked in. 💓
It’s hard to think totally clearly when you’re afraid so don’t beat yourself up over “why didn’t I do this or this.” Glad you’re ok mama! 💜
@rokroya thanks my dear.  We still need to do sushi!
@365curlgirl anytime!
This was important to share. Someone needed to hear this.  You did the right thing...
@lost_in_the_indigo I always knew you were a wise woman. Thank you for supporting me my dear 💗
I am so glad that you’re okay, I know it feels like you needed to do more, but you did what your spidey senses told you too. That’s so scary!
@graygirltraveler 💕💕 i definitely need a fancy "us" date now!

Omg, Crystal. I think you did all the right things. Don't beat yourself up though. It's hard to know for sure what any of us would do when confronted with a situation like that. So glad you were able to get out of there safely.

@rebel.diva imagine!? I can't even think what might have happened if Alex did nothing.  I mean,  a part of me understands,  but most of me didn't get inaction.  I never post about it, but many times ive ridden the train with a random drunk girl and made sure they got home safely, even got off when one was kicked off njtransit and convinced the cops to let me go with her to the hospital.  Im the helper!  I never imagined needing the help but always wondered if someone would step up for me.  I gotta tell myself what i tell my students: people need people... even me.
@365curlgirl yes, we all do, even when we think we don't ❤️😍😘

OMG!! I'm SO GLAD you had a guardian angel there. And it was someone willing to jump in. Someone else might not have! How many times have people sat frozen and watched someone else get abused? So... Just be thankful. Creeps are out there and no matter how fierce or strong, anyone can be in danger in a moment. Big hugs to you. Love you. ❤️
@taz3x no lie cuz, im getting both.  And beggin my doc to finally clear me for mma lol
Pepper spray and a taser , love you cuzzo stay safe out here
@n8tivesoultress sorry it brought out your own anxiety!  But, as someone i know travels alone,  I hope it just reminds you to be an watch for yourself at all times too!

@365curlgirl no apologies needed! I am grateful for you sharing your experience. I am also grateful that you are ok and that Alex was willing to help. It’s a scary world out there and not many people are willing to help a stranger. Thank you love!
Listening to your posts, hearing your fear, girl I have an anxiety. I’m glad you are ok.
@mrs_abroscat thank you Colyn! 💗💗
So sorry this happened to you and so very glad you were not physically  harmed during this incident. 😢❤️
@rev_maria thanks Maria! 💖
Wow! @365curlgirl I am so sorry you had to experience that! Thank God for guy #2!! Glad you are ok!
@michaelpaulclawson indeed!
That’s a terrifying story. Guy 2 is a hero
@slum_baybeee lol naaaah cousin but good lookin' out
@365curlgirl 💯
Do I need to pull-up with the tooly cuzzo!?
@neesh_nini_7218 you're right,  all i know was nothing good was going on i  it.  Thank you my dear! ❤❤
You did the right thing...Dont think about what you should of done and start to regret it. You don't know what was on that man's mind. I'm glad you are safe boo!!
